rpi-self-update (1.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Prevent corrupting a flash by interrupting it. While the image is being
    written, an SSH login now shows a live-progress view with a clear "do not
    interrupt" banner instead of a bare shell, and `restore` refuses to act
    (use `restore --force` to override). Previously a user who SSH'd in
    mid-write and ran `restore` would force-reboot during the dd and leave a
    half-written, unbootable image.
  * Show real progress during the otherwise-silent download/write phase
    (MiB written, from the block device's sysfs stats), so the flash no longer
    looks hung.
  * MOTD no longer unconditionally tells the user to run `restore`.

 -- Gordon Hollingworth <gordon@raspberrypi.com>  Mon, 22 Jun 2026 10:50:07 +0100

rpi-self-update (1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Support 32-bit images and 32<->64-bit switches. Detect the Pi model from
    /proc/device-tree/model and offer matching 32-bit and 64-bit cloud-init
    images; the whole-image flash carries the target architecture.
  * Mirror the running system's SSH password-auth policy onto the flashed
    image (ssh_pwauth true only if sshd currently permits passwords, read via
    sshd -T), instead of always disabling it.
  * Arm a recovery watchdog for the tryboot recovery boot via
    kernel_watchdog_timeout, and disarm it from the initramfs once network and
    SSH are up — so a broken/stuck initramfs self-recovers to the normal OS,
    while a flash in progress can never be reset mid-write.
  * Pin arm_64bit in tryboot.txt to the running kernel's architecture, since
    tryboot.txt replaces config.txt and the recovery initramfs must match.
  * Wait up to 30s for the Ethernet carrier in the initramfs rather than
    checking once (Pi 5 link negotiation is not instant).
  * Select the initramfs dynamic linker by host userland architecture
    (arm64/armhf/armel) instead of hardcoding aarch64.
  * Drop the legacy /boot/ssh first-boot trigger; SSH is enabled via cloud-init.

 -- Gordon Hollingworth <gordon@raspberrypi.com>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 19:43:00 +0100

rpi-self-update (1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix prepare aborting when WiFi PSK is an already-derived 64-hex-char key.
    NetworkManager can return a raw 64-character PSK rather than a plaintext
    passphrase; wpa_passphrase rejects it (8..63 chars only), leaving the hash
    empty and aborting the prepare. Use the raw key verbatim in that case.

 -- Gordon Hollingworth <gordon@raspberrypi.com>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 12:02:39 +0100

